tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, cholesterol, and triglycerides, suggesting impaired glucose tolerance and dyslipidemia. One creatinine value is markedly elevated (3.2 mg/dL), but another is normal (1.0 mg/dL); this discrepancy may indicate a lab error or acute kidney issue-clinical correlation is advised. Total protein is slightly low. Liver enzymes and electrolytes are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and metabolic risk factors.
